        #stage
            br
            p
                a(href="index.html") urtil 
                | is a little tool that generates html pages,
                | similar to the "New Tab" page of Firefox.
            p.    
                When you provide it with a list of webpages like this:
                
            pre.
                github.com
                npmjs.com

            p.    
                It will generate an html page that looks like this:
                
            img(src="./img/tiles.png" width="600")
                
            h2 example config
            p.
                Some notes on the <a href="https://github.com/monsterkodi/urtil/blob/gh-pages/examples/example">config file</a> from the <a href='examples/example.html'>main example</a>:
                
            h4 
                a(href="https://github.com/monsterkodi/urtil/blob/gh-pages/examples/example#L13") example
            pre.
                @                      . ts 300 . fg #fff . bg #555 
                tiles                  . html   . refresh
                    @                  . tw 300 . th 210  . bg #7fc4d2
                    github.com         . -
                    atom.io             
                    electron.atom.io   . -
                    nodejs.org          
                    npmjs.com          . -
                    gulpjs.com           
                    gruntjs.com        . -
            
            p.        
                The first line is the main page setup: 300 pixel square tiles with custom page and title colors.
            p.
                The second line creates a local html file with the title <b>tiles</b>.
            p.
                The <b>tiles</b> page has tiles of size 300x210 and a custom background color.
            p.
                <b>. -</b> means: centers the preceeding tiles and let the next tile begin on a new line.
                
            h4 
                a(href="https://github.com/monsterkodi/urtil/blob/gh-pages/examples/example#L13") useless
            pre.
                useless
                    heeeeeeeey.com                                    
                    thatsthefinger.com                                
                    eelslap.com                                       
                    www.staggeringbeauty.com                          
                    www.republiquedesmangues.fr                       
                    www.movenowthinklater.com                         
                    www.koalastothemax.com                            
                    grandpanoclothes.com                              
                ...
            p.
                This list contains a subset of the links from Tim Holmans 
                <a href='https://github.com/tholman/the-useless-web'>useless-web</a>.
            p.  
                No config section was neccessary here because the defaults are suitable for larger link collections.

            h4 
                a(href="https://github.com/monsterkodi/urtil/blob/gh-pages/examples/example#L44") monsterkodi
            pre.                
                monsterkodi                 . html . - . refresh 
                    @                       . bg #444 . fg #fff . ts 300 . title off
                    monsterkodi.net         . image ../monsterkodi.net.png
                    monsterkodi.github.io
                                            -
                    github.com/monsterkodi
                    npmjs.com/~monsterkodi                      
                                            -
                    projects                . html . - . sh 960 . !
                        @                   . bg #333 . fg white . ts 250

                        monsterkodi.github.io/urtil             
                        monsterkodi.github.io/password-turtle
                        monsterkodi.github.io/knix
                                            -
                        www.npmjs.com/package/strudl
                        www.npmjs.com/package/sds
                        www.npmjs.com/package/noon
                                            -
                        www.npmjs.com/package/color-ls
                        www.npmjs.com/package/colorcat
                        www.npmjs.com/package/konrad
                                            -
                
            p.
                The <b>image</b> keyword (3rd line) can be used to provide an image in case the website doesn't render with the underlying <a href=https://www.npmjs.com/package/webshot>webshot</a>.
            p. 
                Titles are shown by default on hover. <b>title off</b> turns them off completely. <b>title on</b> would show them always.
            p.
                If urtil has created a thumbnail image for a webpage in previous runs, it doesn't regenerate it by default.
                The <b>refresh</b> keyword forces it to regenerate the thumbnail on every run.
                
            p.  
                These config values are available:
            p
                ul
                    li <b>- </b> or <b>break</b>
                    li <b>! </b> or <b>refresh</b>
                    li <b>sh</b> or <b>screenHeight</b>
                    li <b>th</b> or <b>tileHeight</b>
                    li <b>tw</b> or <b>tileWidth</b>
                    li <b>ts</b> or <b>tileSize</b>
                    li <b>bg</b> or <b>bgColor</b>
                    li <b>fg</b> or <b>fgColor</b>
                    li <b>@ </b> or <b>config</b>

